      "properties": {
        "analysisTarget": "GET /api/logs/<user_id>",
        "severity": "critical",
        "summary": "The log retrieval endpoint chains three vulnerabilities: (1) No authentication/authorization allows any caller to access any user's audit logs (IDOR), (2) the user_id path parameter is injected directly into a SQL query enabling full database extraction (SQLi), and (3) raw exception messages are returned to the client aiding attack refinement (Info Disclosure). The audit logs themselves may contain sensitive data such as plaintext passwords logged during login events."
